# Kafka Web API with Kafka Magic – Setup and Usage Guide

---

## 1. Prerequisites

- Java JDK 11+
- Apache Kafka
- Visual Studio / VS Code
- Kafka Magic

---

## 2. Kafka Setup

### 2.1 Start Zookeeper
```cmd
cd kafka\bin\windows
zookeeper-server-start.bat ../config/zookeeper.properties
2.2 Start Kafka Broker
cmd
Copy code
cd kafka\bin\windows
kafka-server-start.bat ../config/server.properties
2.3 Create Kafka Topic
cmd
Copy code
cd kafka\bin\windows
kafka-topics.bat --create --topic product-topic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1
kafka-topics.bat --list --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
3. Run the .NET Web API
Open the project in Visual Studio / VS Code

Ensure Kafka producer points to localhost:9092

Run the API

Test POST /api/kafka/produce in Swagger

4. Kafka Magic Setup
4.1 Register Cluster
Open Kafka Magic → Cluster Explorer → Add New Cluster

Cluster Name: LocalKafka

Bootstrap Servers: localhost:9092

Save cluster

4.2 View Topics
Navigate to the cluster → Topics

Verify product-topic exists

4.3 Consume Messages
Select product-topic → Start Listening

Messages sent from Web API appear in real-time

4.4 Publish Messages (Optional)
Navigate to topic → Publish Message → enter message → send

5. Execution Order
Start Zookeeper

Start Kafka Broker

Verify / create topic

Run .NET Web API

Open Kafka Magic, register cluster, start consuming messages

Test API → messages should appear in Kafka Magic
